                    <a href='@Url.Action("DownloadClientDocument", "Document", new { area = "Documents", enc = EncryptionHelper.Encrypt("clientDocumentId=" + Model.RoiAccidentReportGuidanceNoteClientDocumentationId) })' >
                        Guidance Note 1-3.
                    </a>
                </p>	
            }
            @if (Model.SectionsToShow.Contains(NextStepsSectionEnum.Section2_3))
            {
                <h3>
                    <img src="/Content/images/red-arrow.gif" />Further Information</h3>
                <p>
                    Detailed information about the reporting requirements and associated legislation
                    can be found in
                    <a href='@Url.Action("DownloadClientDocument", "Document", new { area = "Documents", enc = EncryptionHelper.Encrypt("clientDocumentId=" + Model.NiAccidentReportGuidanceNoteClientDocumentationId) })' >
                        Guidance Note 1-3.
                    </a>
                </p>	
            }
            @if (Model.SectionsToShow.Contains(NextStepsSectionEnum.Section3_1))
            {
                <h3>
                    <img src="/Content/images/red-arrow.gif" />Advice</h3>
                <p>
                    In the event of fatal or major accident, whatever the time of day or night, you
                    should contact the Peninsula 24 Hour Advice Line (0844 892 2772) so that they can
                    guide you through management of the incident.<br />
                    The Advice Line is also available to help you in the event of other incidents however
                    large or small.</p>	
            }
            @if (Model.SectionsToShow.Contains(NextStepsSectionEnum.Section3_2))
            {
                <h3>
                    <img src="/Content/images/red-arrow.gif" />Advice</h3>
                <p>
                    In the event of fatal or major accident, whatever the time of day or night, you
                    should contact the Peninsula 24 Hour Advice Line (01 855 5050) so that they can
                    guide you through management of the incident.<br />
                    The Advice Line is also available to help you in the event of other incidents however
                    large or small.</p>	
            }
            @if (Model.SectionsToShow.Contains(NextStepsSectionEnum.Section3_3))
            {
                <h3>
                    <img src="/Content/images/red-arrow.gif" />Advice</h3>
                <p>
                    In the event of fatal or major accident, whatever the time of day or night, you
                    should contact the Peninsula 24 Hour Advice Line (0844 892 2786) so that they can
                    guide you through management of the incident.<br />
                    The Advice Line is also available to help you in the event of other incidents however
                    large or small.
                </p>
            }
            @if (Model.SectionsToShow.Contains(NextStepsSectionEnum.Section4_1))
            {
                <h3>
                    <img src="/Content/images/red-arrow.gif" />Reporting to the Enforcing Authorities</h3>
                <h4>
                    In England, Scotland and Wales</h4>
                <p>
                    Fatal and major injuries and those that make the injured employee absent from or
                    unable to carry out their normal work for more than 7 days must be reported to the
                    enforcing authorities. Injuries to people who are not employed which result in them
                    being taken from the site of an accident directly to hospital must also be reported.<br />
                    Fatal injuries, major injuries and injuries to members of the public should be reported
                    by phone as soon as it is practicably possible. The number for the HSE’s Incident
                    Reporting Line is 0845 300 9923; Out of hours fatal and multiple injuries should
                    be reported to the HSE duty officer on 0151 922 9235, Subsequently, and within 10
                    days, the initial report must be supplemented by a more detailed report submitted
                    online.<br />
                    Injuries which lead to an employee being unable to work or do their normal duties
                    for more than 7 days have to be reported online within 15 days of the accident.<br />
                    <br />
                    Go to the <a href="https://extranet.hse.gov.uk/lfserver/external/F2508IE">HSE Incident
                                  Reporting Website</a> and make your report. Before you do so you may wish to
                    open a <a href='@Url.Action("DownloadClientDocument", "Document", new { area = "Documents", enc = EncryptionHelper.Encrypt("clientDocumentId=" + Model.GbOnlineAccidentReportFormClientDocumentationId) })'>
                               template </a>of the form that you will be required to complete. It will help
                    ensure that you have all of the required information to hand and can complete the
                    report in one go.
                </p>
            }
            @if (Model.SectionsToShow.Contains(NextStepsSectionEnum.Section4_2))
            {
                <h3>
                    <img src="/Content/images/red-arrow.gif" />Reporting to the Enforcing Authorities</h3>
                <h4>
                    In Northern Ireland</h4>
                <p>
                    Fatal injuries and those that make the injured employee absent from or unable to
                    carry out their normal work for more than 3 days must be reported to the HSENI.
                    Injuries to people who are not employed which result in them being taken from the
                    site of an accident directly to hospital must also be reported.<br />
                    Fatal injuries, major injuries and injuries to members of the public should be reported
                    by phone as soon as it is practicably possible. Subsequently, and within 10 days,
                    the initial report must be supplemented by a more detailed report online at the
                    <a href="https://www.secure.hseni.gov.uk/forms/NI2508.aspx">HSENI Incident Reporting Website</a>
                    or as hard copy on <a href='@Url.Action("DownloadClientDocument", "Document", new { area = "Documents", enc = EncryptionHelper.Encrypt("clientDocumentId=" + Model.NiOnlineAccidentReportFormClientDocumentationId) })'>
                                           Form NI2508. </a>
                    <br />
                    Injuries which lead to an employee being unable to work or do their normal duties
                    for more than 3 days must also be reported <a href="https://www.secure.hseni.gov.uk/forms/NI2508.aspx">
                                                                   online</a> or on <a href='@Url.Action("DownloadClientDocument", "Document", new { area = "Documents", enc = EncryptionHelper.Encrypt("clientDocumentId=" + Model.NiOnlineAccidentReportFormClientDocumentationId) })'>
                                                                                        Form NI2508 </a>within 10 days of the accident.
                </p>
            }
            @if (Model.SectionsToShow.Contains(NextStepsSectionEnum.Section4_3))
            {
                <h3>
                    <img src="/Content/images/red-arrow.gif" />Advice</h3>
                <h4>
                    In Ireland</h4>
                <p>
                    Fatal injuries and those that make the injured employee absent from or unable to
                    carry out their normal work for more than 3 days must be reported to the HSA. Injuries
                    to people who are not employed which result in them receiving treatment by a registered
                    medical practitioner or at a hospital must also be reported.<br />
                    Brief details about fatal injuries should be reported by phone on 1890 289 389 as
                    soon as it is practicably possible. A written report on <a href='@Url.Action("DownloadClientDocument", "Document", new { area = "Documents", enc = EncryptionHelper.Encrypt("clientDocumentId=" + Model.RoiOnlineAccidentReportFormClientDocumentationId) })'>
                                                                                Form IR1 </a>or an <a href="https://webapps.hsa.ie/CIRW/index.php">online report</a>
                    giving further detail should be made as soon as possible after the incident. Other
                    reportable accidents should also be notified <a href="https://webapps.hsa.ie/CIRW/index.php">
                                                                     online</a> or on <a href='@Url.Action("DownloadClientDocument", "Document", new { area = "Documents", enc = EncryptionHelper.Encrypt("clientDocumentId=" + Model.RoiOnlineAccidentReportFormClientDocumentationId) })'>
                                                                                          Form IR1 </a>as soon as possible.
                </p> 
            }
            @if (Model.SectionsToShow.Contains(NextStepsSectionEnum.Section4_4))
            {
                <h3>
                    <img src="/Content/images/red-arrow.gif" />Reporting to the Enforcing Authorities</h3>
                <h4>
                    In Guernsey</h4>
                <p>
                    Fatal injuries and those that make the injured employee absent from or unable to
                    carry out their normal work for more than 3 days must be reported to the Guernsey
                    HSE. Injuries to people who are not employed which result in them being taken from
                    the site of an accident directly to hospital must also be reported.<br />
                    Fatal injuries and injuries to members of the public should be reported by phone
                    as soon as it is practicably possible. Subsequently, and within 7 days, the initial
                    report must be supplemented in writing on an <a href="http://www.hse.gg/PDFs/HSEReportIDDO1.pdf">
                                                                     official form</a>. Injuries which lead to an employee being unable to work or
                    do their normal duties for more than 3 days must also be reported within 7 days
                    on the <a href="http://www.hse.gg/PDFs/HSEReportIDDO1.pdf">official form</a>.
                </p>
            }
            @if (Model.SectionsToShow.Contains(NextStepsSectionEnum.Section4_5))
            {
                <h3>
                    <img src="/Content/images/red-arrow.gif" />Reporting to the Enforcing Authorities</h3>
                <h4>
                    In Jersey</h4>
                <p>
                    There is no reporting requirement.
                </p>
            }
            @if (Model.SectionsToShow.Contains(NextStepsSectionEnum.Section4_6))
            {
                <h3>
                    <img src="/Content/images/red-arrow.gif" />Reporting to the Enforcing Authorities</h3>
                <h4>
                    In the Isle of Man</h4>
                <p>
                    Fatal and major injuries to any person and those that cause an employee to be absent
                    from or unable to carry out their normal work for more than 3 days must be reported
                    to the Isle of Man Health and Safety at Work Inspectorate.
                    <br />
                    Fatal and major injuries should be reported by phone as soon as it is practicably
                    possible; call 01624 685881 or 07624 313626 out of hours or <a href="http://www.gov.im/transport/msd/healthandsafety/injuryreport.aspx">
                                                                                    online</a>. Subsequently, and within 7 days, the initial report must be supplemented
                    in writing on an <a href='@Url.Action("DownloadClientDocument", "Document", new { area = "Documents", enc = EncryptionHelper.Encrypt("clientDocumentId=" + Model.IomOnlineAccidentReportFormClientDocumentationId) })' >
                                         official form </a>.<br />
                    Injuries which lead to an employee being unable to work or do their normal duties
                    for more than 3 days must also be reported within 7 days on the <a href='@Url.Action("DownloadClientDocument", "Document", new { area = "Documents", enc = EncryptionHelper.Encrypt("clientDocumentId=" + Model.IomOnlineAccidentReportFormClientDocumentationId) })' >
                                                                                        official form </a>.
                </p>
            }
                <div class="offset10">
